                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13559840" author="eromeiro" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2013 18:29:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am working on a patch for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13561879" author="eromeiro" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2013 19:12:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Made admin controllers keep track of referring page id so user is returned to the workspace they came from. Tests were added&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13572607" author="eromeiro" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2013 17:44:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;any chance someone can take a look at this in the next few days?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13572816" author="raminder" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2013 20:57:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Eduardo, Sorry it got missed some how. Thanks for the reminder. I will take a look at the patch today evening or tomorrow. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573341" author="javafrog" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 09:29:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still doesn&apos;t work for me =/&lt;br/&gt;
Example flow:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Switch to workspace &quot;abc&quot; (from &quot;Main&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
2. Go to admin interface&lt;br/&gt;
3. Go &quot;Back to Rave&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
4. I&apos;m again on workspace &quot;Main&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573475" author="eromeiro" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 13:26:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Matthias,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It works here on my end using the example flow you described. Is it possible the patch wasnt applied correctly when you tested it? Can anyone else verify this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573534" author="javafrog" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 14:28:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am terribly sorry, the patch had indeed not been applied correctly.&lt;br/&gt;
However, now I get several exceptions during normal use. For example, in rave-portal-resources/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/jsp/views/store.jsp the line &amp;lt;c:when test=&quot;${empty searchTerm and (empty widgets or widgets.totalResults eq 0)}&quot;&amp;gt; is added so it exists twice, leading to corrupt XML and thus exceptions. Or maybe I did another stupid thing with the patch &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573547" author="eromeiro" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 14:46:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for checking. I will look into the exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573770" author="eromeiro" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 18:49:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I removed that duplicate test in store.jsp; i dont know how that got there :$. I went through every other page and did not get any exceptions related to this patch. Please find the new patch attached for your review. Thanks for your time and let me know if anything else comes up.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13573921" author="raminder" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 20:56:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am able to test the patch and it worked well. I have concerned about the amount of changes needed to pass the reference id. I know we are following similar approach in Widget store. Can we find a better solution to pass parameter around? Something in the user session context etc. Ideas? I am ok to apply this patch and create a new task to think about improvement. Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573934" author="eromeiro" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 21:14:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In doing the patch I did follow the similar approach of the widget store and the other areas the reference id is passed. I do agree with your point about the improvement task and will begin to look into a better overall solution. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573945" author="geerzo" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 21:22:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with Eduardo, this is very similar to how we do it elsewhere. That doesn&apos;t mean it&apos;s a great way, but it is similar. As long as it works, I&apos;d say apply it and then put in a ticket to improve the flow in both places.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573947" author="raminder" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 21:24:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. I will apply the patch and create task for improvement. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573968" author="raminder" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 21:47:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch. Thanks Eduardo for the patch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13574375" author="javafrog" created="Fri, 8 Feb 2013 10:45:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay, works for me!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
